<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/13.9> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:13.9" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/13.0> ;
    skos:definition "Determining the impacts of environmental health and safety. Create and implement the EHS program. Train and educate employees of the EHS function. Oversee and manage the EHS program."@en,
        "Determining the impacts of 环境健康与安全. 创建 and implement the EHS program. Train and educate employees of the EHS function. Oversee and manage the EHS program."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "13.9" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Environmental Health and Safety (EHS)"@en,
        "管理 环境健康与安全 (EHS)"@zh ;
    opf:domain "management_support" ;
    opf:level 2 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.1.3.5> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:2.1.3.5" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.1.3> ;
    skos:definition "Aligning regulatory activities related to managing industry requirements. Train employees on regulatory requirements. Records for the appropriate regulatory agencies must be maintained and the new product process must be approved by the appropriate regulatory body before it is published to the organization. The submission lifecycle - i.e. creation, review, and approval of the submission and its components must be managed in a collaborative fashion."@en ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "2.1.3.5" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage regulatory requirements"@en,
        "管理 regulatory requirements"@zh ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 4 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.2.1> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:2.2.1" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.2> ;
    skos:definition "Coordinating R&D activity to identify new technologies to integrate into the revamped portfolio of products/services. This is inclusive of all forms of new and evolving technology such as artificial intelligence (AI). Conduct early-stage R&D activity to close gaps between existing solution offerings and changing market expectations. Triangulate appropriate technologies that can support the development of a revised product/service portfolio."@en,
        "Coordinating R&D activity to identify new technologies to integrate into the revamped portfolio of products/services. This is inclusive of all forms of new and evolving technology such as 人工智能 (AI). 开展 early-stage R&D activity to close gaps between existing solution offerings and changing market expectations. Triangulate appropriate technologies that can support the development of a revised product/service portfolio."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "2.2.1" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Perform discovery research"@en ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 3 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.2.3> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:2.2.3" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.2> ;
    skos:definition "Encompassing the identification and capture of new product/service requirements or potential improvements to current products/services. Collaborating with members of the supply chain to ensure the feasibility of what is being defined in the requirements. For example, a product with manufacturing requirements that supply chain cannot currently fulfill requires a corporate decision to either upgrade manufacturing capabilities or abandon the new product. Enterprise-level effects and needs must be considered. Depending on the nature of the final product or service, these requirements are often defined as a set of abilities, such as availability or reliability, that influence product development decisions."@en,
        "Encompassing the identification and capture of new product/service requirements or potential improvements to current products/services. Collaborating with members of the 供应链 to ensure the feasibility of what is being defined in the requirements. For example, a product with manufacturing requirements that 供应链 cannot currently 履约 requires a corporate decision to either upgrade manufacturing capabilities or abandon the new product. Enterprise-level effects and needs must be considered. Depending on the nature of the final product or service, these requirements are often defined as a set of abilities, such as 可用性 or reliability, that influence product development decisions."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "2.2.3" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define product/service development requirements"@en,
        "定义 product/service development requirements"@zh ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 3 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.4> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "ITIL:V5:Business Analysis" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/2.0> ;
    skos:definition "ITIL V5 practice: Business Analysis. Mapped to Develop and Manage Products and Services."@en,
        "ITIL V5 practice: 业务分析. Mapped to 开发 and 管理 产品和服务."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "2.4" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Business Analysis"@en,
        "业务分析"@zh ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 2 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.1> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:3.1" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.0> ;
    skos:definition "Making sense of the market and customers to identify the right opportunities to be capitalized, given the organization's competencies. Discern trends and shift in the market and customers. Identify the right market opportunities that fit closely with the organization's capabilities and strategy by gathering intelligence on various attributes of different market/customer segments."@en,
        "Making sense of the market and customers to identify the right opportunities to be capitalized, given the organization's competencies. Discern trends and shift in the market and customers. 识别 the right market opportunities that fit closely with the organization's capabilities and 战略 by gathering intelligence on various attributes of different market/customer segments."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "3.1" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Understand markets, customers, and capabilities"@en ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 2 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.2.1> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:3.2.1" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.2> ;
    skos:definition "Refining the attributes of organizational offerings to define their value proposition for the customer. Clearly define the suite of offerings in terms of the value delivered, from the perspective of what the customer desires. Validate the benefits delivered to the customers against target market segments, using techniques such as minimum viable product. Position brands for the respective products/services, in line with their unique value proposition and aligned with customers needs."@en,
        "Refining the attributes of organizational offerings to define their value proposition for the customer. Clearly define the suite of offerings in terms of the value delivered, from the perspective of what the customer desires. 验证 the benefits delivered to the customers against target market segments, using techniques such as minimum viable product. Position brands for the respective products/services, in line with their unique value proposition and aligned with customers needs."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "3.2.1" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define offering and customer value proposition"@en,
        "定义 offering and customer value proposition"@zh ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 3 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.2.4.7> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:3.2.4.7" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.2.4> ;
    skos:definition "Coordinating marketing and distribution efforts across different channels that integrate well with each other, are in conformance with company values, visual identity and branding, and offer uniform customer service experience that drives customer loyalty and repeat business."@en,
        "Coordinating marketing and distribution efforts across different channels that integrate well with each other, are in conformance with company values, visual identity and branding, and offer uniform 客户服务 experience that drives customer loyalty and repeat business."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "3.2.4.7" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Orchestrate seamless customer experience across supported channels"@en,
        "编排 seamless customer experience across supported channels"@zh ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 4 .

<https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.5.5.1> a skos:Concept,
        opf:ProcessNode ;
    dcterms:source "PCF:3.5.5.1" ;
    skos:broader <https://oprocess.net/opf/node/3.5.5> ;
    skos:definition "Imparting guidance and instruction to sales partners/alliances concerning products/services. Distribute literature about the organization's products/services. Conduct workshops. Disseminate useful media content to engage and enlighten partners. Create communities through group engagements."@en,
        "Imparting guidance and instruction to sales partners/alliances concerning products/services. Distribute literature about the organization's products/services. 开展 workshops. Disseminate useful media 内容 to engage and enlighten partners. 创建 communities through group engagements."@zh ;
    skos:inScheme <https://oprocess.net/opf> ;
    skos:notation "3.5.5.1" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Provide sales and product/service training to sales partners/alliances"@en,
        "提供 sales and product/service 训练 to sales partners/alliances"@zh ;
    opf:domain "operating" ;
    opf:level 4 .

